                "institute": "3CPRLNZ"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The T-400 Intense Neutron Generator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The samples of Mo and Al as foils 20 mm in diameter",
                "were 99.99% and 99.999% purity, and 0.2 and 0.1 mm in",
                "thickness. Groups of samples were placed at 0 to 150",
                "degree relative to the beam direction and centered",
                "about the T-Ti target at distances of 4-9.3 cm. The",
                "Mo sample in each group was sandwiched between two Al",
                "foils."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " An effective deuteron beam energy and beam",
                "current is 360 keV and about 2 mA. T-Ti taret was",
                "around 1.6 mg/cm2 thick. Neutron yield is around",
                "1~2E11 n/s. The neutron energies for various",
                "directions were determined by cross section ratios of",
                "90-Zr(n,2n)89m+g-Zr and 93-Nb(n,2n)92m-Nb."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A CH8403 coaxial high-purity germanium",
                "detector with a relative efficiency of 20% and an",
                "energy resolution of 2.6 keV at 1.33 MeV. The",
                "efficiency was calibrated by a standard gamma-source,",
                "standard reference material 4275 from the National",
                "Institute of Standards and Technology. In gamma ray",
                "measurement, the distance between sample and HPGe is",
                "2 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The irradiation was lasted 1~4 hours, the",
                "angle is 45 degree between deuteron beam and target."
              ]
            }
          ],
